{"title": "AVL Tree", "summary": "A self-balancing Binary Search Tree where the difference between heights of left and right subtrees cannot be more than one for all nodes.", "key_points": ["Strictly balanced, guarantees O(log n) search.", "Uses Left, Right, Left-Right, and Right-Left rotations.", "Height balanced factor ranges from -1 to 1."], "code": {"c": "struct Node *rightRotate(struct Node *y) {
