{"title": "Quick Sort", "summary": "An efficient, divide-and-conquer sorting algorithm that partitions an array around a selected pivot element.", "key_points": ["Average time complexity O(n log n).", "In-place sorting algorithm.", "Not a stable sort by default."], "code": {"c": "int partition(int arr[], int low, int high) {
    int pivot = arr[high];
    int i = (low - 1);
    for (int j = low; j <= high - 1; j++) {
        if (arr[j] < pivot) {
            i++;
            swap(&arr[i], &arr[j]);
        }
    }
    swap(&arr[i + 1], &arr[high]);
    return (i + 1);
}", "python": "def partition(arr, low, high):
    pivot = arr[high]
    i = low - 1
    for j in range(low, high):
        if arr[j] < pivot:
