    arr[i + 1], arr[high] = arr[high], arr[i + 1]
    return i + 1"}, "execution_steps": ["1. Choose a pivot element from the array.", "2. Partition the array so all elements smaller than pivot are left, and larger are right.", "3. Recursively apply the same logic to the left and right sub-arrays."], "variants": ["Merge Sort", "Heap Sort"], "visual_hooks": ["target_pivot(index)", "animate_partition_swap(idx1, idx2)"], "reasoning_map": {"problem": "Algorithms like Bubble or Insertion sort are too slow (O(n^2)) for large datasets.", "solution": "Use divide-and-conquer to partition and sort sub-arrays independently.", "tradeoffs": "Worst case O(n^2) if poorly pivoted, but usually outperforms Merge Sort due to cache locality."}}

