{"title": "Rehashing", "summary": "The process of resizing a hash table and re-inserting all elements using a new hash function when load factor exceeds a threshold.", "key_points": ["Triggered when load factor > 0.7 typically.", "Creates a new table, usually double the size.", "All elements must be re-hashed into the new table."], "code": {"python": "def rehash(old_table):
