{"title": "Splay Tree", "summary": "A self-adjusting BST that moves recently accessed elements to the root via splaying, achieving amortized O(log n) operations.", "key_points": ["No explicit balance condition.", "Recently used nodes move to root — good temporal locality.", "Amortized O(log n) for access, insertion, deletion."], "code": {"python": "def splay(root, key):
