{"title": "Expression Tree", "summary": "A binary tree that represents a mathematical or logical expression, where leaves are operands and internal nodes are operators.", "key_points": ["In-order traversal gives infix expression.", "Pre-order gives prefix (Polish) notation.", "Post-order gives postfix (Reverse Polish) notation."], "code": {"python": "def evaluate(node):
    if node is None:
        return 0
    if node.left is None and node.right is None:
        return int(node.val)
    left = evaluate(node.left)
    right = evaluate(node.right)
    if node.val == '+': return left + right
    if node.val == '-': return left - right
    if node.val == '*': return left * right
    if node.val == '/': return left // right"}, "execution_steps": ["1. Parse expression tokens.", "2. Operators become internal nodes; operands become leaves.", "3. Recursively evaluate left subtree, then right subtree.", "4. Apply operator to results and return."], "variants": ["Binary Tree", "BST"], "visual_hooks": ["highlight_operator_node(node)", "animate_evaluation(tree)"], "reasoning_map": {"problem": "Need structured computation of complex expressions.", "solution": "Represent operator precedence hierarchically in a tree.", "tradeoffs": "N/A — primarily a compiler/calculator construct."}}

