{"title": "Circular Queue", "summary": "A queue implementation using a fixed-size array where the rear wraps around to the front, efficiently reusing freed slots.", "key_points": ["Avoids wasted space of standard array-based queue.", "Full condition: (rear + 1) % size == front.", "Used in CPU scheduling, buffering."], "code": {"c": "void enqueue(int queue[], int *front, int *rear, int size, int val) {
