{"title": "BFS (Breadth First Search)", "summary": "A graph traversal algorithm that explores nodes level by level using a queue, guaranteeing shortest path in unweighted graphs.", "key_points": ["Uses a queue for level-order traversal.", "Time complexity O(V + E).", "Finds shortest path in unweighted graphs."], "code": {"c": "void bfs(int graph[][V], int start) {
